    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-03-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-03-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="229" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d229">
                <head>No. 225.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Noyes</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 17,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is indicated to me that there are impediments to entry of pork products
                        shipped before the date of prohibitory decree. Insist energetically that all
                        shipments made before date of decree shall be received on proper inspection,
                        as otherwise great hardship will result to American shippers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>BLAINE, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
